Trade/Device Name(s): VALIDATE® Urine Chemistry Calibration Verification Test Sets
Document Summary: FDA 510(k) summary for VALIDATE Urine Chemistry Calibration Verification Test Sets, a quality control material for verifying calibration, validating reportable ranges, and determining linearity in clinical chemistry systems.
Indications for Use Summary: Used by laboratory professionals to quantitatively verify calibration, validate reportable ranges, and determine linearity in automated, semi-automated, and manual chemistry systems for listed analytes.
